article.headline: Wofford 74, Georgia Southern 65
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- Noah Dahlman scored 26 points on 10-of-10 shooting from the field as Wofford held off Georgia Southern 74-65 on Wednesday night. Dahlman, who has scored in double figures in 63 consecutive games for the Terriers (7-9, 4-1 Southern Conference), was also 6 of 8 from the free-throw line. Wofford, which has won four straight in the series, led 30-26 at halftime. The Eagles (4-14, 0-5) opened the second half with a Jelani Hewitt jumper to get within two points, but the Terriers pulled away. Trailing by 14, Georgia Southern scored seven straight points to make it 64-57 with 43 seconds left, but Wofford hit 11 of 11 free throws to send the Eagles to their fifth straight loss. Terry Martin added 15 points and Kevin Giltner had 10 for the Terriers, who were 21 of 27 from the free-throw line. Ben Drayton led Georgia Southern with 15 points and Zuri James had 14.
